1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Oh, yeah, I got a big box. Yes, I do.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:04,500
I got a big box. How about you?

3
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:06,000
I got a big box. Yes, I do.

4
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,500
I got a big box. How about you?

5
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:09,000
I think you don't know what you're saying.

6
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:11,500
It is from Sabre, our new owner,

7
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:14,500
and it is to Sabre us.

8
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:16,000
I wonder what's inside.

9
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,500
Scissor me.

10
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,500
Dunder Mifflin was recently bought

11
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:27,500
by an electronics company named Sabre.

12
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:29,500
They stepped in at the 11th hour.

13
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:32,000
And they saved our asses.

14
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Although David Wallace said

15
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,000
that we were the one branch

16
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,000
that was actually working right,

17
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
so we probably could have saved our own asses.

18
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,500
We didn't need them touching our asses.

19
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,500
Ow! Ow! Ow!

20
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:46,500
Wow! Awesome!

21
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:50,000
For accounting, a brand-new print-off.

22
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
And for the sales staff,

23
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,500
a new fax machine.

24
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:58,500
This cord has Creed written all over it.

25
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:04,000
And whoever would like a brand-new scanner

26
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,000
can come visit it in my office.

27
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Thank you. Here we go.

28
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Oh! Oh!

29
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Wow! Cool. What next?

30
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Uh, who's Gabe?

31
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
This note says to put the box aside

32
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,000
for a Gabe Lewis who's coming tomorrow.

33
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Okay, everybody, listen up.

34
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
I have some bad news.

35
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Due to circumstances beyond my control,

36
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,500
impulsivity and inattention to detail...

37
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,500
Hey, hey.

38
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:34,500
I have opened a box which should not have been opened...

39
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:35,500
Terrible mistake.

40
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:36,500
...and distributed things

41
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:37,500
which should not have been distributed.

42
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:38,500
Undistributable.

43
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:40,500
Well, maybe we can put the box back together.

44
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:43,500
Impossible. He opened it like an ape.

45
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:45,500
I think we can do it.

46
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,500
Yeah. Yeah.

47
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:50,500
Hmm.

48
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:52,500
Did we try printer first?

49
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:54,500
Shredder at an angle? Yeah.

50
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:56,500
Fax cable, then the scanner upside down?

51
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:58,000
Yes.
